Definitions

"Paper Account" refers to a simulated, non-live, or demo trading account
provided by Interactive Brokers or similar platforms, where no real funds or
assets are transacted or at risk. "Live Account" refers to an account involving
real funds or assets used for actual trading or transactions through Interactive
 Brokers or similar platforms.

